steps.instruction:
Made by [Rick Martinez](https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/churros-with-bittersweet-chocolate-sauce)

### Sauce
1. Scrape vanilla seeds into a small saucepan; discard pod
2. Add cream, brown sugar, cocoa powder, espresso powder, and salt and cook over medium-high heat, whisking occasionally, until sugar is dissolved, no lumps of cocoa powder remain, and mixture is simmering, about 4 minutes
3. Remove from heat and add chocolate, stirring to melt
4. Keep warm over very low heat until ready to serve

### Churros
1. Fit pastry bag with star tip. Whisk cinnamon and 1 cup organic sugar in a medium bowl; set aside
2. Bring vanilla bean, milk, butter, salt, remaining 1 Tbsp. organic sugar, and ½ cup water to a simmer in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat
3. Using a wooden spoon, add flour in one go, and vigorously mix until dough comes together, about 30 seconds
4. Transfer to the bowl of a stand mixer or a large bowl; discard vanilla bean. Let cool slightly
5. Using a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment on medium-low speed, add eggs to dough, one at a time, making sure to incorporate each egg before adding the next (alternatively, stir vigorously with a wooden spoon)
6. Dough will look broken at first; continue to beat, scraping bowl occasionally, until dough is smooth, glossy, and somewhat stretchy (pull off a small piece of dough and stretch it—it shouldn't break). Spoon dough into prepared pastry bag.
7. Pour oil into a large pot to come halfway up the sides
8. Fit pot with thermometer and heat over medium-high until thermometer registers 350°
9. Holding bag at an angle so tip is a few inches above surface of oil, squeeze out dough, moving the bag as you squeeze so dough is piped in a 6" length into oil
10. Using a paring knife, cut off dough at the tip to release into oil
11. Repeat process to make 4 more dough lengths
12.  Fry churros, turning once and adjusting heat as needed to maintain oil temperature, until golden brown on all sides, 2–3 minutes per side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined baking sheet. Repeat with remaining dough.
